        # SQL query to get billing data grouped by hospital
query1 = """
        SELECT 
            h.Hospital_ID,
            h.Name AS Hospital_Name,
            SUM(b.Amount) AS Total_Billing_Amount
        FROM 
            BILLING b
        JOIN 
            ADMISSION a ON b.Admission_ID = a.Admission_ID
        JOIN 
            HOSPITAL h ON a.Hospital_ID = h.Hospital_ID
        GROUP BY 
            h.Hospital_ID, h.Name
        ORDER BY 
            Total_Billing_Amount DESC;
        """

  # SQL query to get monthly billing data
query2 = """
        SELECT 
            h.Hospital_ID,
            h.Name AS Hospital_Name,
            YEAR(b.Billing_Date) AS Year,
            MONTH(b.Billing_Date) AS Month,
            SUM(b.Amount) AS Monthly_Billing
        FROM 
            BILLING b
        JOIN 
            ADMISSION a ON b.Admission_ID = a.Admission_ID
        JOIN 
            HOSPITAL h ON a.Hospital_ID = h.Hospital_ID
        GROUP BY 
            h.Hospital_ID, h.Name, YEAR(b.Billing_Date), MONTH(b.Billing_Date)
        ORDER BY 
            h.Hospital_ID, Year, Month;
        """

# SQL query to get yearly billing data
query3 = """
SELECT 
    h.Hospital_ID,
    h.Name AS Hospital_Name,
    YEAR(b.Billing_Date) AS Year,
    SUM(b.Amount) AS Yearly_Billing
FROM 
    BILLING b
JOIN 
    ADMISSION a ON b.Admission_ID = a.Admission_ID
JOIN 
    HOSPITAL h ON a.Hospital_ID = h.Hospital_ID
GROUP BY 
    h.Hospital_ID, h.Name, YEAR(b.Billing_Date)
ORDER BY 
    h.Hospital_ID, Year;
"""

# Execute the query
cursor.execute(query3)

# Fetch all results
results3 = cursor.fetchall()

# Create a Pandas DataFrame from the query results
df3 = pd.DataFrame(results3, columns=['Hospital_ID', 'Hospital_Name', 'Year', 'Yearly_Billing'])

# Print the DataFrame to verify
print(df3)

# Plot yearly billing for all hospitals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

# Group data by hospitals
hospitals = df3['Hospital_Name'].unique()

for hospital in hospitals:
    hospital_data = df3[df3['Hospital_Name'] == hospital]
    plt.plot(
        hospital_data['Year'], 
        hospital_data['Yearly_Billing'], 
        marker='o', 
        label=hospital
    )

# Customize the plot
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Yearly Billing Amount')
plt.title('Yearly Billing for All Hospitals')
plt.xticks(df3['Year'].unique())  # Set unique years as x-axis ticks
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# SQL query to get average billing amount for each hospital
query4 = """
SELECT 
    h.Hospital_ID,
    h.Name AS Hospital_Name,
    AVG(b.Amount) AS Average_Billing_Amount
FROM 
    BILLING b
JOIN 
    ADMISSION a ON b.Admission_ID = a.Admission_ID
JOIN 
    HOSPITAL h ON a.Hospital_ID = h.Hospital_ID
GROUP BY 
    h.Hospital_ID, h.Name
ORDER BY 
    Average_Billing_Amount DESC;
"""

# Execute the query
cursor.execute(query4)

# Fetch all results
results4 = cursor.fetchall()

# Create a Pandas DataFrame from the query results
df4 = pd.DataFrame(results4, columns=['Hospital_ID', 'Hospital_Name', 'Average_Billing_Amount'])

# Print the DataFrame to verify
print(df4)

# Plot average billing amount for each hospital
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

# Bar plot
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
plt.bar(df4['Hospital_Name'], df4['Average_Billing_Amount'], color='skyblue')
x_labels = df4['Hospital_Name']
step = 25  # Show every 25th label
x_ticks = range(0, len(x_labels), step)
plt.xticks(ticks=x_ticks, labels=x_labels[x_ticks], rotation=45, ha='right')

# Customize the plot
plt.xlabel('Hospital Name')
plt.ylabel('Average Billing Amount')
plt.title('Average Billing Amount by Hospital')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')  # Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
plt.tight_layout()

# SQL query to find the month with the highest billing for each hospital
query5 = """
WITH MonthlyBilling AS (
    SELECT 
        h.Hospital_ID,
        h.Name AS Hospital_Name,
        YEAR(b.Billing_Date) AS Year,
        MONTH(b.Billing_Date) AS Month,
        SUM(b.Amount) AS Monthly_Billing
    FROM 
        BILLING b
    JOIN 
        ADMISSION a ON b.Admission_ID = a.Admission_ID
    JOIN 
        HOSPITAL h ON a.Hospital_ID = h.Hospital_ID
    GROUP BY 
        h.Hospital_ID, h.Name, YEAR(b.Billing_Date), MONTH(b.Billing_Date)
)
SELECT 
    Hospital_ID,
    Hospital_Name,
    Year,
    Month,
    Monthly_Billing
FROM 
    MonthlyBilling
WHERE 
    Monthly_Billing = (SELECT MAX(Monthly_Billing) 
                       FROM MonthlyBilling m 
                       WHERE m.Hospital_ID = MonthlyBilling.Hospital_ID);
"""

# Execute the query
cursor.execute(query5)

# Fetch all results
results5 = cursor.fetchall()
print(len(results5))
# Create a Pandas DataFrame from the query results
df5 = pd.DataFrame(results5, columns=['Hospital_ID', 'Hospital_Name', 'Year', 'Month', 'Monthly_Billing'])

# Print the DataFrame to verify
print(df5)

# Plot the results: Monthly billing with the highest amount for each hospital
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))

# Plotting the data
plt.barh(df5['Hospital_Name'], df5['Monthly_Billing'], color='skyblue')
step = 25  # Show every 25th label
y_ticks = range(0, len(y_labels), step)
plt.yticks(ticks=y_ticks, labels=y_labels[y_ticks])
# Customize the plot
plt.xlabel('Monthly Billing Amount')
plt.ylabel('Hospital Name')
plt.title('Month with Highest Billing Amount for Each Hospital')
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()

query6="""WITH MonthlyBilling AS (
    SELECT 
        h.Hospital_ID,
        h.Name AS Hospital_Name,
        YEAR(b.Billing_Date) AS Year,
        MONTH(b.Billing_Date) AS Month,
        SUM(b.Amount) AS Monthly_Billing
    FROM 
        BILLING b
    JOIN 
        ADMISSION a ON b.Admission_ID = a.Admission_ID
    JOIN 
        HOSPITAL h ON a.Hospital_ID = h.Hospital_ID
    GROUP BY 
        h.Hospital_ID, h.Name, YEAR(b.Billing_Date), MONTH(b.Billing_Date)
)
SELECT 
    mb.Hospital_ID,
    mb.Hospital_Name,
    mb.Year,
    mb.Month,
    mb.Monthly_Billing
FROM 
    MonthlyBilling mb
JOIN (
    SELECT 
        Hospital_ID,
        Year,
        MAX(Monthly_Billing) AS Max_Billing
    FROM 
        MonthlyBilling
    GROUP BY 
        Hospital_ID, Year
) AS MaxMonthly ON mb.Hospital_ID = MaxMonthly.Hospital_ID 
                 AND mb.Year = MaxMonthly.Year 
                 AND mb.Monthly_Billing = MaxMonthly.Max_Billing;

"""
# Execute the query
cursor.execute(query6)

results6 = cursor.fetchall()
print(len(results6))

    h.Hospital_ID,
    h.Name AS Hospital_Name,
    YEAR(a.Date_of_Admission) AS Year,
    MONTH(a.Date_of_Admission) AS Month,
    COUNT(a.Date_of_Admission) AS Number_of_Patients

query8 = """
SELECT 
    h.Hospital_ID,
    h.Name AS Hospital_Name,
    YEAR(a.Date_of_Admission) AS Year,
    AVG(DATEDIFF(a.Date_of_Discharge, a.Date_of_Admission)) AS Average_Length_of_Stay
FROM 
    HOSPITAL h
JOIN 
    ADMISSION a ON h.Hospital_ID = a.Hospital_ID
WHERE 
    a.Date_of_Discharge IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY 
    h.Hospital_ID, h.Name, YEAR(a.Date_of_Admission)
ORDER BY 
    Year, h.Hospital_ID;
"""

# Function to get a free port
def get_free_port():
    sock = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)
    sock.bind(('localhost', 0))
    port = sock.getsockname()[1]
    sock.close()
    return port

# Function to run the Dash app
def run_app(app):
    port = get_free_port()
    threading.Thread(
        target=app.run_server,
        kwargs={"host": "127.0.0.1", "port": port, "debug": True, "use_reloader": False},
        daemon=True,
    ).start()
    webbrowser.open_new_tab(f"http://127.0.0.1:{port}")

@app.callback(
    [Output('modal', 'style'), Output('overlay', 'style'),Output('bg','style'),Output('h1','style')],
    [Input(f'view-details-{i}', 'n_clicks') for i in range(1, 4)],
    [Input('close-modal', 'n_clicks')]
)
def toggle_modal(*args):
    ctx = callback_context
    if not ctx.triggered:
        return {'display': 'none'}, {'display': 'none'},{'display': 'block'},{'display': 'block'}

    triggered_id = ctx.triggered_id
    if triggered_id and 'view-details' in triggered_id:
        # Show modal when a button is clicked
        return {
            'display': 'block'
        }, {
            'display': 'block'
        },{
            'display': 'none'
        },{
            'display': 'none'
        }
        
    elif triggered_id == 'close-modal':
        # Close modal when the close button is clicked
        return {
            'display': 'none'
        }, {
            'display': 'none'
        }, {
            'display': 'block'
        }, {
            'display': 'block'
        }

        title="Monthly Billing", color='Year'
    )

    hospital_df3["Year"] = hospital_df3["Year"].astype(str)
    unique_years = sorted(hospital_df3["Year"].unique())
    yearly_billing_fig = px.bar(
        hospital_df3,
        x='Year', y='Yearly_Billing',
        title="Yearly Billing",
        labels={"Year": "Year", "Yearly_Billing": "Billing Amount"},
        category_orders={"Year": unique_years},
        color='Year'
    )
    
    monthly_highest_fig = px.bar(
                hospital_df6,
                x='Year',
                y='Monthly_Billing',
                color='Month',
                title='Monthly Billing Over Time',
                labels={'Month': 'Month', 'Monthly_Billing': 'Monthly Billing ($)', 'Hospital_Name': 'Hospital Name'},
                category_orders={"Year": unique_years},
                orientation='v'
            )
            
            
  

    return total_billing_fig, monthly_billing_fig, yearly_billing_fig, monthly_highest_fig

def update_modal_graphs(selected_hospital):

    # Filter data for the selected hospital
    hospital_df1 = df1[df1['Hospital_Name'] == selected_hospital]
    hospital_df2 = df2[df2['Hospital_Name'] == selected_hospital]
    hospital_df3 = df3[df3['Hospital_Name'] == selected_hospital]
    hospital_df5 = df5[df5['Hospital_Name'] == selected_hospital]
    hospital_df7 = df7[df7['Hospital_Name'] == selected_hospital]
    hospital_df8 = df8[df8['Hospital_Name'] == selected_hospital]

    # Generate figures
    number_of_patients_fig = px.line(
            hospital_df7, x='Month', y='Number_of_Patients',
            title="Number of Patients",color='Year'
        )

    average_stay_fig = px.pie(
    hospital_df8,
    names='Year',  # The column for different sections of the pie
    values='Average_Length_of_Stay',  # The column for the size of each section
    title="Average Length of Stay by Year",
    # textinfo='value',  # Show the actual values as labels on the pie chart
)
    average_stay_fig.update_traces(textinfo='value')


    return number_of_patients_fig,average_stay_fig

query9 = """
SELECT 
    YEAR(date_of_admission) AS year,  
    MONTH(date_of_admission) AS month,  
    COUNT(*) AS total_admissions  
FROM 
    Admission
GROUP BY 
    YEAR(date_of_admission), MONTH(date_of_admission)  
ORDER BY 
    year, month;  
"""

cursor.execute(query9)

# Convert the results into a DataFrame

query10 = """
SELECT 
    YEAR(a.Date_of_Admission) AS Year,  
    a.Admission_Type,                 
    AVG(b.Amount) AS Average_Billing   
FROM 
    ADMISSION a
JOIN 
    BILLING b ON a.Admission_ID = b.Admission_ID
GROUP BY 
    YEAR(a.Date_of_Admission), a.Admission_Type 
ORDER BY 
    Year;  
         
 
"""

cursor.execute(query10)

# Fetch all results
results10 = cursor.fetchall()


df10 = pd.DataFrame(results10, columns=['Year', 'Admission_Type', 'Average_Billing'])

# # Convert the results into a DataFrame
